- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and provides an FPT algorithm and a kernel. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the problem involves trees, which can be seen as a special case of graphs, and cutting edges. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper deals with combinatorial optimization and graph theory. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the problem can be seen as a game between two players, where one tries to cut edges to disconnect the other's paths.
